WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.880
Hi, I'm Isabel. I'm a software engineer, and today we're going to get Quarto set up on your computer.

00:00:04.960 --> 00:00:12.800
You'll start out by going to quarto.org, click on Get Started on their homepage, and download the Quarto CLI tool.

00:00:13.320 --> 00:00:18.040
In VS Code, you'll create a new file and name it whatever you want with .qmd at the end.

00:00:18.639 --> 00:00:22.040
I'd also recommend downloading the Quarto extension in VS Code.

00:00:22.040 --> 00:00:27.879
It gives you buttons to click to preview your files and syntax highlighting and a lot of other nice stuff.

00:00:28.440 --> 00:00:32.560
Once we're back in our file, we're gonna have to specify a output format.

00:00:32.560 --> 00:00:39.919
Let's start out by just creating an HTML web page. This will be great for publishing, reports, or whatever else we want to share.

00:00:40.119 --> 00:00:46.080
We're just gonna create a few headings. We'll say hello. We'll add some Python code, and let's press Preview.

00:00:46.759 --> 00:00:51.880
If Quarto generates HTML, we see right in VS Code, or I can pop it out and look at it as a local website.

00:00:51.880 --> 00:00:59.680
To change from a website to a presentation, I change the format from HTML to reveal.js and press Preview again.

